🧭 Clear Project Architecture

| Layer         | Tech                        | Role                 |
| ------------- | --------------------------- | -------------------- |
| **Frontend**  | HTML + Bootstrap + Flask    | Auth, Pages          |
| **Backend**   | Flask + SQLAlchemy          | Auth, Routing, DB    |
| **ML Models** | scikit-learn, XGBoost etc   | Disease prediction   |
| **Dashboard** | Streamlit                   | User reports, charts |
| **Storage**   | SQLite (initially)          | User, Reports        |
| **Extras**    | Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn | Charting in reports  |

🧩 Step-by-Step Development Plan
| Phase | Feature                                 | Tech               |
| ----- | --------------------------------------- | ------------------ |
| 1️⃣   | Basic Flask app + login/signup          | Flask + SQLAlchemy |
| 2️⃣   | Add dashboard (after login)             | Bootstrap + Jinja  |
| 3️⃣   | Integrate 2 ML models (Diabetes, Heart) | scikit-learn       |
| 4️⃣   | Create prediction form + show result    | HTML + Flask       |
| 5️⃣   | Generate + store report                 | Matplotlib + DB    |
| 6️⃣   | Embed Streamlit dashboard               | Streamlit          |
| 7️⃣   | Polish UI + Add more models             | CSS + ML           |


🏗️ Project Modules Overview
🔐 1. User Authentication (Flask + SQLAlchemy)
Signup/Login system

Dashboard after login

User session maintained

🧪 2. ML Model Prediction Interface
User selects model (e.g., Diabetes)

Enters required fields via form

Model runs and returns prediction + insights

📄 3. Auto-Generated Report (PDF/HTML)
Charts + prediction + conclusion

Stored in DB with timestamp

Can download or revisit later

📊 4. Streamlit Dashboard
View past predictions

Visual summary (charts, trends)

Simple filters (e.g., by date, type)

📂 Data Flow (Simplified)

User logs in → Dashboard → Selects ML tool (e.g. Diabetes)
 → Inputs data → Model runs → Result + Graphs generated
 → Report saved → User can view in Streamlit


